sentence: Tuesday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 5,283.40.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.6 billion.
Declining stocks led advancers by 2.16 to 1 ratio.
There were 899 advancers and 1943 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 33 stocks reached a 52 week high and 44 reaching lows.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed down -.38% for the day; a total of -18.52 points.
T-Mobile US, Inc. ( TMUS ) had the largest percent change down (-3.11%) while Mylan N.V. ( MYL ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.98%.
The Dow Jones index closed down -.3% for the day; a total of -53.76 points.
Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change down (-3.47%) while Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change gain rising 3.41%.
